Implementation on Flask Setup Flask:

To install Flask, type!pip install Flask in your Google Colab notebook.
Make an App for Flask:

Launch the application and import Flask.
Explain Routes:

Make routes to manage the various phases of the conversation, such as email collection and greeting.
Make Templates in HTML:

Create the design templates that Flask will use to render the chatbot's interface.
Launch Flask:

To launch the Flask app, add if __name__ == '__main__': app.run().
Communicate with Chatbots:

To communicate with the chatbot, open a web browser and click the provided link.
Preferable: Install on a server:

For public access, make use of systems like Heroku, AWS, or Google Cloud. For deployment, consult the relevant platform documentation.







